This paper deals with secure query processing over encrypted data, which is a common topic in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on processing k Nearest Neighbors (kNN) queries, which involves database management (cs.DB) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The proposed solution also involves analyzing and manipulating data structures, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents experimental results to showcase the efficiency of the proposed scheme, which is a common practice in software engineering (cs.SE).
